1
00:00:09,040 --> 00:00:14,040
Look, I know. You both have
lives here, beautiful, messy lives.

2
00:00:14,080 --> 00:00:18,040
That is what makes you so fabulously human.

3
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:22,040
You don't want to give
them up. I understand.

4
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:25,040
Actually, it's you they
can't give up, Doctor.

5
00:00:26,540 --> 00:00:28,540
And I don't think they should.

6
00:00:28,980 --> 00:00:30,940
Go with him.

7
00:00:30,980 --> 00:00:33,725
Go save every world you can find.

8
00:00:33,750 --> 00:00:36,505
Who else has that chance?

9
00:00:36,530 --> 00:00:38,940
Life will still be here.

10
00:00:38,980 --> 00:00:39,983
You could come, Brian.

11
00:00:40,008 --> 00:00:42,940
Somebody's got to water the plants.

12
00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:02,900
Dear Dad, this is the difficult bit.

13
00:02:04,014 --> 00:02:06,311
If I've got this right, you're
reading this letter a week

14
00:02:06,336 --> 00:02:07,900
after we left in the TARDIS.

15
00:02:07,940 --> 00:02:11,900
The thing is, we're not coming back.

16
00:02:12,650 --> 00:02:16,899
We're alive and well and stuck.

17
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:21,900
In New York, 50 years before I
was born, we can't come home again.

18
00:02:22,196 --> 00:02:26,900
I won't ever see you again,
and that breaks my heart.

19
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:30,900
I'm so sorry, Dad.

20
00:02:33,566 --> 00:02:35,296
I thought about this for years,

21
00:02:35,321 --> 00:02:38,900
and I realised there
was one thing I could do.

22
00:02:39,283 --> 00:02:43,899
I could write to you, tell you
everything about how we lived,

23
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:46,900
how, despite it all, we were happy.

24
00:02:46,940 --> 00:02:49,570
But before I do, I need you to know...

25
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:53,900
you are the best dad
any son could have had.

26
00:02:54,803 --> 00:02:58,778
And for all the times I drove
you mad and you drove me mad,

27
00:02:58,803 --> 00:03:00,443
all the times I snapped at you...

28
00:03:02,625 --> 00:03:03,625
...I'm sorry.

29
00:03:05,465 --> 00:03:06,900
I miss everything about you.

30
00:03:08,721 --> 00:03:10,720
Especially our awkward hugs.

31
00:03:12,420 --> 00:03:16,420
I bought a trowel. We
have a small yard. I garden.

32
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:24,300
But one more important bit of business.

33
00:03:24,340 --> 00:03:26,270
The man who delivered the letter, Anthony.

34
00:03:26,796 --> 00:03:28,456
Be nice to him.

35
00:03:29,467 --> 00:03:31,467
Cos he's your grandson.

36
00:03:48,526 --> 00:03:51,711
We finally adopted in 1946.

37
00:03:52,258 --> 00:03:54,217
Anthony Brian Williams,

38
00:03:55,085 --> 00:03:58,064
he can tell you everything.
He'll have the family albums.

39
00:03:58,110 --> 00:04:01,070
And I realise having a
grandson who's older than you

40
00:04:01,095 --> 00:04:03,055
is so far beyond weird.

41
00:04:03,125 --> 00:04:05,085
But I'm sorry.

42
00:04:07,484 --> 00:04:09,484
I love you, Dad.

43
00:04:10,552 --> 00:04:12,552
I miss you.

